{
  "texts": [
    "Authorship is a dynamic category which is constantly irritated by multiple factors, technology being only one of many (others may include personality (reviewers), economy, religion, law etc.",
    "), the eco-systemic dynamic is crystallized in the closure of (scientific) authorship as a system.",
    "Therefore, scientific authorship practices have continuity through vicarious learning within disciplines, where individuals adapt these practices to their unique contexts and experiences.",
    "This adaptation occurs as authors become part of a community of practice, engaging in shared activities and gradually mastering the norms and conventions of their field (Lave and Wenger 1991).",
    "Through this participatory process, authorship practices are transmitted, refined, and personalized, ensuring both continuity and individual expression within the scientific community."
  ]
}